subSubSection.paragraph:
H o l o t y p e. Designated here. S136786 (Torres Vedras sample 44; figured 
Text-fig. 25a, d, e
).

Many pollen grains, all of the same kind, occur entangled in the trichomes on the surface of all the fruits (
Text-fig. 25d–g
). The pollen is circular to elliptic in equatorial outline, about 16 µm in diameter and monocolpate. The colpus is short, about 6 µm long and does not reach the equator. The grains are tectate with an irregular rugulate surface covered by closely spaced and solitary microechinae (
Text-fig. 25d–g
). The colpus membrane is covered by small verrucae (
Text-fig. 25f, g
).
